1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,877
<i>Who exactly is this Emil?</i>

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:06,172
<i>He said your family wronged him.</i>

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:07,549
<i>Particularly your husband.</i>

4
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:10,844
<i>What are you looking for?</i>
<i>Whose locker is this?</i>

5
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,345
<i>This belonged to one of my staff,</i>

6
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,139
<i>who turned out to be Emil's daughter.</i>

7
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:15,849
<i>Did Greta say where she was going?</i>

8
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:18,601
<i>Liam, we tried to stop your mother.</i>

9
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:19,894
<i>But she wouldn't let us.</i>

10
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:22,230
<i>There's so many of you here,</i>
<i>but you didn't stop her?</i>

11
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:24,607
<i>Seriously, Liam?</i>
<i>So much has already happened!</i>

12
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:27,110
<i>Why don't you try thinking of ways</i>
<i>to get off this island?</i>

13
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:29,654
<i>Emil needs to be gone.</i>

14
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:31,322
<i>Don't you see?</i>

15
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,824
<i>He doesn't listen to you!</i>

16
00:00:32,907 --> 00:00:36,036
<i>If I were you, I'd strike first.</i>

17
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,370
[OFFICER] <i>Sebastian.</i>

18
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:39,497
<i>You're free.</i>

19
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:45,170
<i>We need to find the hostages.</i>
<i>Especially the senator's son.</i>

20
00:00:45,253 --> 00:00:49,007
<i>As long as he knows</i>
<i>we're holding his son hostage,</i>

21
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>he won't let the police storm the island.</i>

22
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:54,471
<i>Senator.</i>

23
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:56,347
<i>I have your brother with me.</i>

24
00:00:58,308 --> 00:00:59,309
<i>Homer.</i>

25
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:01,269
- [GRUNTING]
<i>- Homer.</i>

26
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:03,188
- [GUNSHOTS]
<i>- Homer!</i>

27
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:04,397
<i>Don't try to follow me!</i>

28
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:06,483
<i>Damn you, Senator!</i>

29
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:09,110
<i>If something bad happens to my brother,</i>

30
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:11,362
<i>I will kill your entire clan!</i>

31
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:13,573
<i>- Where's the money?</i>
<i>- They have it.</i>

32
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:15,450
<i>I need you to do one more thing.</i>

33
00:01:16,951 --> 00:01:17,994
<i>Let's stop this, Pa.</i>

34
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:20,080
<i>You already got a lot of money, right?</i>

35
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:21,456
<i>Isn't it enough?</i>

36
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:23,750
<i>This wasn't just about money.</i>

37
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,835
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

38
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,128
<i>Leni?</i>

39
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:28,880
<i>Leni, dear!</i>

40
00:01:29,672 --> 00:01:31,090
<i>What…? Leni!</i>

41
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:42,185
Dude,

42
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:43,728
I want to apologize again.

43
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:47,232
I was also there
when your mom insisted she'd stay.

44
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,235
But I couldn't do anything.

45
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:53,363
But you didn't say
to just leave her on her own.

46
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:57,200
That's what Auntie Wendy said, right?

47
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,620
To leave Mama on her own?

48
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,415
[MAGNUS EXHALES DEEPLY]

49
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:09,337
[SIGHS] You and Olsen should talk.

50
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:11,673
What if Emil already has Mama?

51
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:15,468
Pa, from what we know of him,
he'll definitely harm Mama.

52
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:17,470
He might even kill her!

53
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:21,307
So Auntie Wendy shouldn't have
decided to leave her.

54
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:24,185
Olsen isn't wrong.

55
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,731
And you can't blame his mother
for what happened.

56
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,693
Really, Pa?

57
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:33,570
You're still siding with him?

58
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,446
Even after this has happened?

59
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:38,658
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:40,034
[EMIL] <i>You tricked her!</i>

61
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:42,162
<i>You fooled Ayen!</i>

62
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:45,415
<i>Do you remember the crap</i>
<i>you did to my daughter?</i>

63
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,750
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

64
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:52,255
If there's someone
who should be blamed for what's happening,

65
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:55,300
it's me.

66
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:58,261
- [SCOFFS]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

67
00:02:58,344 --> 00:02:59,762
[OLSEN] Why, Sir Magnus?

68
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:04,642
Why should we blame you?

69
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:11,608
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

70
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:15,987
Mike has a plan to save all of us.

71
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:44,098
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

72
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:54,442
Leni!

73
00:03:55,985 --> 00:03:57,904
Boss, what happened?

74
00:03:58,529 --> 00:04:00,114
My daughter isn't waking up.

75
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:02,200
Leni! Wake up!

76
00:04:02,283 --> 00:04:04,035
Boss, we have another problem.

77
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:08,915
The police or military
might attack us anytime now.

78
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:10,124
Why?

79
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,043
What happened?

80
00:04:12,126 --> 00:04:14,921
I talked to Senator Eduardo.

81
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:20,760
Homer is out of jail, but everything got
messy when I couldn't show him his son.

82
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:23,721
[LUCAS] Homer fought back,
and they exchanged fire.

83
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:26,474
The line got disconnected.
Now I can't contact him!

84
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:37,277
I need to bring my daughter
to the hospital.

85
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,195
I know, sir.

86
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,239
But how are we going to do that

87
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:43,700
if we get attacked by the police?

88
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:50,456
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:08,850
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,422
[MAGNUS] We're not safe here anymore.

91
00:05:40,381 --> 00:05:41,591
We're too exposed.

92
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:45,178
You need to evacuate.

93
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:48,639
If we continue walking down this path,

94
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:51,392
we'll reach an old construction site.

95
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,812
It was an old project of ours
that was never completed.

96
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:57,440
Anyway, we can use it as a hideout

97
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:59,192
until rescue comes.

98
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:01,194
[MAGNUS] So, okay.

99
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,863
You must go now.

100
00:06:03,946 --> 00:06:05,323
Come on.

101
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:06,574
[WENDY] You're not coming?

102
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:13,956
I will do everything I can
to save all of you

103
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,667
because you're my responsibility.

104
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,545
You're going to stay here?

105
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:21,172
[LIAM] Pa.

106
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:23,341
What are you planning to do?

107
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,762
I'll talk to the leader
of the hostage takers,

108
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:30,139
and I will negotiate with them.

109
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,557
Sir, wait a second.

110
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:33,184
That's dangerous.

111
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:34,811
[WENDY] Magnus.

112
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:38,940
Do you really think he'll listen to you
after everything that's happened?

113
00:06:39,023 --> 00:06:40,691
I don't understand. Why--

114
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,235
I have to do this, Wendy.

115
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:46,739
Liam, stay here. Olsen, you too.
Protect all of them.

116
00:06:48,407 --> 00:06:49,575
[MAGNUS] Okay?

117
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:51,619
Go! You must go now!

118
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:58,376
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:03,131
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,841
[REPORTER] <i>The police and the military</i>

121
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:08,511
<i>are preparing an extensive attack</i>

122
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:11,806
<i>against the hostage takers</i>
<i>at La Playa Roja,</i>

123
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:15,017
<i>while the authorities are taking in</i>

124
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,562
<i>the rescued hostages from the island.</i>

125
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:19,439
<i>According to police reports,</i>

126
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:22,775
<i>a lot of civilians</i>
<i>are still trapped there,</i>

127
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:26,612
<i>including the son</i>
<i>of Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>

128
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,114
<i>Macky Maristella,</i>

129
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:29,782
<i>and the Roja family.</i>

130
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:36,247
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:50,928
[WENDY] Magnus.

132
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:01,189
[MAGNUS EXHALES DEEPLY]

133
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:05,526
You're putting yourself in danger, sir.

134
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,904
Are you sure about this?

135
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:11,032
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

136
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:13,284
If that's the case, sir,

137
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,161
then you'll need this.

138
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:25,546
Chief Ben.

139
00:08:27,131 --> 00:08:27,965
Thank you.

140
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,592
Yes, sir.

141
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:31,636
Take care of them.

142
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,931
[WENDY] Magnus.

143
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,684
You know they will kill you.

144
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:42,438
Can't we just wait for rescue to come?

145
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:45,441
I have to find Greta, Wendy.

146
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,195
I'm sorry.

147
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:53,824
You did what you could.

148
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,744
Don't blame yourself.

149
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,915
Like I said earlier…

150
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:08,256
I take full responsibility
for all that is happening now.

151
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:12,426
How are you responsible for all of this?

152
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:15,096
I have to go.

153
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:19,392
Be careful, sir.

154
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:26,107
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

155
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,001
- Liam.
- I'm coming with you.

156
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,962
No. Son, this is my battle.

157
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,964
Nope. This is our battle.

158
00:09:50,047 --> 00:09:51,966
This is our family's battle.

159
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:54,468
No, it is mine.

160
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:56,512
Go back with them.

161
00:09:59,473 --> 00:10:01,017
You know me.

162
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:03,227
I'm stubborn.

163
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,563
Since when did I listen to what you say?

164
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:09,191
I won't just sit here
while Mama's in danger

165
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:11,402
wherever she is.

166
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:17,783
[MOTOR BOAT RUMBLING]

167
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:24,874
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:29,837
[LIAM] Pa.

169
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,213
Hey, careful.

170
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:34,133
Liam.

171
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:35,676
How is it?

172
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:41,390
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:10:57,865 --> 00:10:59,325
[MIKE] Hurry. Come on.

174
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:08,668
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:30,523
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,026
Come here.

177
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:52,670
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

178
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:56,006
[MIKE] Come on.

179
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,216
[MINNIE] Go to Luna.

180
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,802
You're going down.

181
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:16,861
This was supposed to be a railroad tunnel.

182
00:12:17,611 --> 00:12:19,572
They won't be able to find us here.

183
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:33,627
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

184
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,343
[LIAM GRUNTS SOFTLY]

185
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:42,595
Pa.

186
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,390
[GRUNTS]

187
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:55,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:04,992
[LIAM GRUNTS]

189
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,411
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

190
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:13,918
Go.

191
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:21,217
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:34,313
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC FADES]

193
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:43,155
- [MIKE EXHALES DEEPLY]
- Daddy.

194
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:45,741
Are we really safe here?

195
00:13:45,824 --> 00:13:47,076
Yes, dear.

196
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:49,245
You should rest.

197
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:54,583
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,834
[MIKE GRUNTS]

199
00:13:58,254 --> 00:13:59,505
How are you feeling, hon?

200
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,006
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

201
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,508
Much better.

202
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:04,718
Thank you. We're safe now.

203
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:11,767
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,519
[BEN EXHALES DEEPLY]

205
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:17,731
I didn't know Olsen
went through all of that.

206
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:20,192
I also found out

207
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:24,613
that I have a lot of things
I don't know about our family.

208
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:29,910
About you and Magnus…

209
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:32,788
Is it really over?

210
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:36,041
Pa--

211
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:38,210
You said it was already over.

212
00:14:38,794 --> 00:14:39,837
Dear,

213
00:14:40,754 --> 00:14:42,506
I can feel it's not over yet.

214
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:48,846
Maybe that's why Ma'am Greta
is so mad at you.

215
00:14:48,929 --> 00:14:50,973
Because she sees

216
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:53,893
and feels it too.

217
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:56,520
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:58,564
[VOICE QUIVERS]

219
00:14:58,647 --> 00:14:59,815
[SNIFFLES]

220
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:02,735
Do you still love Magnus?

221
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:08,616
How about Olsen's father?

222
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:11,327
Did you love him too?

223
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:15,289
I've made plenty
of wrong decisions in life, Pa.

224
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:21,462
You said you didn't know
that man was a criminal.

225
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,466
I didn't tell Olsen about that either.

226
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:31,764
What else are you hiding
from me and Olsen?

227
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,224
You said

228
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:39,688
you left that man
because he was a criminal.

229
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:43,901
I was already pregnant
with Olsen at the time.

230
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:47,071
Dear…

231
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:49,073
Uh…

232
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:52,117
When you returned home to me,

233
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:55,871
you said that Olsen's father
was already dead.

234
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:58,540
Is he really dead already?

235
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,501
Pa…

236
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:06,048
[INHALES DEEPLY]
Do we really have to talk about him?

237
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,174
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

238
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:08,634
You know, dear…

239
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:16,225
I didn't know you were
hiding so many things from me.

240
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:22,815
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYS]

241
00:16:22,898 --> 00:16:25,275
They're almost done with the trap.

242
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,159
[OLSEN] Is it long enough?

243
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:36,412
Yes. Give me the other end.

244
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,331
All right. Perfect.

245
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:43,502
I got it.

246
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:45,504
Lay it down.

247
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:49,883
[OLSEN GRUNTS]
When those animals find us,

248
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:52,261
let's lead them here.

249
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:55,723
They'll die for sure
if they fall down there.

250
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,975
That's a very good idea, Olsen.

251
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,604
So what, are we really going to stay here?

252
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:06,400
What about Liam and Mr. Roja?
What if they need help?

253
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:09,445
You're worried about Liam?

254
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:13,365
Is it wrong of me to get worried?

255
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,243
So many have died, Luna.

256
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:18,579
What, you want more casualties?

257
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:23,876
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:25,794
You can go. We'll finish up here.

259
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:35,304
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

260
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,599
- [SCREAMS WILDLY]
- [GUNSHOTS]

261
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,853
[PANTING LOUDLY]

262
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:44,354
[DADO] After him!

263
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:56,450
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [PANTING]

264
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,534
Hey!

265
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:01,455
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [MACKY] Help! Help!

266
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:03,874
[GUNSHOTS]

267
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:04,792
Catch him! Hurry!

268
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:10,964
- Ice, Luna, get inside. Take cover.
- [MACKY] Help!

269
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:17,262
[DISTANT GUNSHOTS]

270
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:21,725
Help! Help! [PANTING]

271
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:22,643
[OLSEN] Sir Macky!

272
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,521
- [FIN] Wait! Wait! That's a trap, sir!
- [OLSEN] No, stop!

273
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:32,402
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC SWELLS]

274
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,244
<i>Help! Help!</i> [PANTING]

275
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:44,790
- [OLSEN] <i>Sir Macky! No, stop!</i>
- [FIN]<i> Wait! Wait! That's a trap, sir!</i>

276
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,834
<i>- They're after me!</i>
<i>- Wait! Wait!</i>

277
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:48,794
<i>If you move, you'll fall into our trap!</i>

278
00:18:48,877 --> 00:18:50,629
<i>You'll be impaled, sir!</i>

279
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:54,466
<i>What was that?</i>

280
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:56,760
<i>Olsen and Fin need backup.</i>

281
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:58,595
<i>They found us.</i>

282
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:02,641
[JACINTO] <i>We need to find Emil</i>
<i>and get rid of him.</i>

283
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:05,477
<i>Have you seen Emil?</i>

284
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:07,187
[GOON] <i>Why do you want</i>
<i>Sir Emil dead?</i>

285
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:10,399
<i>That's not part of our agreement.</i>

286
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:11,942
<i>He didn't keep his word.</i>

287
00:19:12,025 --> 00:19:13,735
<i>Why sentence him to death right away?</i>

288
00:19:15,696 --> 00:19:19,366
[LUCAS LAUGHS SINISTERLY]

289
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:21,910
<i>Don't move!</i>

290
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:24,329
[GUNSHOTS]

291
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:26,832
<i>- He might have Mama!</i>
<i>- Liam! Liam!</i>

292
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,750
[EXPLOSION, GUNSHOTS]

293
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:30,294
- [JACINTO] <i>Greta!</i>
<i>- What's going on?</i>

294
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,671
<i>We have to go. They've turned on me.</i>

295
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:34,882
<i>- What?!</i>
<i>- We don't have time for this. Come on!</i>

296
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:37,134
<i>Don't go with him, Ma!</i>

297
00:19:37,217 --> 00:19:39,386
<i>Get away from my mom, or I'll shoot!</i>

298
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,346
[LOUD THUD]

299
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:44,474
[BOTH GRUNTING]

300
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,602
[JACINTO] <i>Drop your gun.</i>

301
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,103
<i>Listen to your mother!</i>

302
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,938
<i>Greta.</i>

303
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,524
<i>Explain everything to your son!</i>

304
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:54,318
<i>What do you need to explain, Ma?</i>

305
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:03,660
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
